{"type": "bundle", "id": "bundle--a57e945d-8e68-5cbb-a810-ed95c9004f7c", "objects": [{"type": "identity", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "created": "2026-05-17T02:33:08Z", "modified": "2026-05-17T02:33:08Z", "name": "VigilIntel", "identity_class": "organization"}, {"type": "marking-definition", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "definition_type": "tlp", "definition": {"tlp": "clear"}}, {"type": "extension-definition", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "extension-definition--f8d78575-edfd-406e-8e84-6162a8450f5b", "name": "PAP", "description": "This defines PAP as a STIX extension", "created": "2022-10-01T00:00:00.000Z", "modified": "2022-10-01T00:00:00.000Z", "schema": "https://github.com/oasis-open/cti-stix-common-objects/tree/master/extension-definition-specifications/pap", "version": "1.0.0", "extension_types": ["property-extension"]}, {"type": "marking-definition", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92", "created": "2022-10-01T00:00:00.000Z", "name": "PAP:CLEAR", "extensions": {"extension-definition--f8d78575-edfd-406e-8e84-6162a8450f5b": {"extension_type": "property-extension", "pap": "clear"}}}, {"type": "note", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "note--6b60d362-5986-51db-88a1-35baf643b738", "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "content": "## Summary\n**FR:** La p\u00e9riode se caract\u00e9rise par une intensification des op\u00e9rations de sabotage \u00e9tatique et de cyberespionnage furtif. La d\u00e9couverte du framework 'Fast16' r\u00e9v\u00e8le une lign\u00e9e conceptuelle de sabotage industriel pr\u00e9datant Stuxnet, ciblant sp\u00e9cifiquement la recherche nucl\u00e9aire. En parall\u00e8le, l'\u00e9volution du botnet Kazuar par l'acteur Turla d\u00e9montre une sophistication accrue dans la communication Peer-to-Peer pour assurer une persistence ind\u00e9tectable. Les attaques de la cha\u00eene d'approvisionnement (OpenAI/TanStack) et l'exploitation massive de failles dans les outils d'administration (Quest KACE) soulignent la vuln\u00e9rabilit\u00e9 critique des infrastructures de d\u00e9veloppement et de gestion centralis\u00e9e. Enfin, le succ\u00e8s record de Pwn2Own Berlin 2026 avec 47 zero-days illustre une course \u00e0 l'armement cyber continue o\u00f9 les technologies d'IA (Codex, Claude) deviennent des cibles prioritaires.\n\n**EN:** The period is characterized by an intensification of state-sponsored sabotage and stealthy cyberespionage operations. The discovery of the 'Fast16' framework reveals a conceptual lineage of industrial sabotage predating Stuxnet, specifically targeting nuclear research. In parallel, the evolution of the Kazuar botnet by the Turla actor demonstrates increased sophistication in Peer-to-Peer communication to ensure undetectable persistence. Supply chain attacks (OpenAI/TanStack) and massive exploitation of flaws in administration tools (Quest KACE) highlight the critical vulnerability of development and centralized management infrastructures. Finally, the record success of Pwn2Own Berlin 2026 with 47 zero-days illustrates a continuous cyber arms race where AI technologies (Codex, Claude) are becoming priority targets.\n", "object_refs": ["identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea"], "abstract": "Strategic | Daily brief (2026-05-17)", "labels": ["strategic", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--1f7bdd77-2102-50d8-a858-ed36fdd98640", "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "note--6b60d362-5986-51db-88a1-35baf643b738", "target_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "description": "Strategic note linked to referenced object", "labels": ["strategic", "note-link", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "note", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "note--7fb8e7a1-24d5-5784-ae6e-72a5417c2d1f", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "content": "## Summary\n**FR:** D\u00e9couverte du framework Fast16, con\u00e7u pour saboter la recherche sur les armes nucl\u00e9aires en alt\u00e9rant les tenseurs de contrainte dans les logiciels de simulation comme LS-DYNA. Cet outil pr\u00e9c\u00e8de conceptuellement Stuxnet.\n\n**EN:** Discovery of the Fast16 framework, designed to sabotage nuclear weapons research by altering stress tensors in simulation software like LS-DYNA. This tool conceptually predates Stuxnet.\n\n## Context\n- Date: 2026-05-16\n- Sector: ['Infrastructures critiques', 'Gouvernement et D\u00e9fense'] / ['Critical_Infrastructure', 'Government_and_Defense']\n- Theme: Sabotage strat\u00e9gique par alt\u00e9ration de simulations physiques / Strategic Sabotage of Physics Simulations\n\n## Tags\nfast16, sabotage, nuclear, ics\n\n## Sources\n- hxxps://www[.]security[.]com/threat-intelligence/fast16-nuclear-sabotage\n", "object_refs": ["identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea"], "abstract": "Geopolitical | Sabotage strat\u00e9gique par alt\u00e9ration de simulations physiques (2026-05-16)", "external_references": [{"source_name": "source", "url": "hxxps://www[.]security[.]com/threat-intelligence/fast16-nuclear-sabotage"}], "labels": ["fast16", "sabotage", "nuclear", "ics", "geopolitical", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--77010c3b-e818-5a64-b793-20ce06bd02f3", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "note--7fb8e7a1-24d5-5784-ae6e-72a5417c2d1f", "target_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "description": "Geopolitical note linked to referenced object", "labels": ["fast16", "sabotage", "nuclear", "ics", "geopolitical", "note-link", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "threat-actor", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "threat-actor--71d345dd-e791-5866-873a-cc571c0f48ad", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "name": "TeamPCP", "threat_actor_types": ["unknown"], "labels": ["threat-actor", "supply chain", "openai", "npm", "breach", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "identity", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "identity--9dc18f4c-569a-5eec-ba61-40453db739f8", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "name": "OpenAI", "identity_class": "organization", "labels": ["victim", "supply chain", "openai", "npm", "breach", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--f9781b01-2f15-50a9-a164-92870063ae8a", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "targets", "source_ref": "threat-actor--71d345dd-e791-5866-873a-cc571c0f48ad", "target_ref": "identity--9dc18f4c-569a-5eec-ba61-40453db739f8", "labels": ["breach", "supply chain", "openai", "npm", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "note", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "note--877d756c-12dc-5aa6-b4a1-ed06f067d8c9", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "content": "## Summary\n**FR:** Attaque de la cha\u00eene d'approvisionnement via des paquets npm malveillants (TanStack) ciblant les employ\u00e9s d'OpenAI. A entra\u00een\u00e9 l'exfiltration de certificats de signature et de secrets internes.\n\n**EN:** Supply chain attack via malicious npm packages (TanStack) targeting OpenAI employees. Resulted in the exfiltration of signing certificates and internal secrets.\n\n## Context\n- Date: 2026-05-16\n- Victim: OpenAI\n- Threat actor: TeamPCP\n- Sector: ['Technologies et T\u00e9l\u00e9coms'] / ['Technology_and_Telecom']\n\n## Tags\nsupply chain, openai, npm\n\n## Sources\n- hxxps://securityaffairs[.]com/192222/hacking/openai-hit-by-supply-chain-attack-linked-to-malicious-tanstack-packages[.]html\n", "object_refs": ["threat-actor--71d345dd-e791-5866-873a-cc571c0f48ad", "identity--9dc18f4c-569a-5eec-ba61-40453db739f8"], "abstract": "Breach | OpenAI (2026-05-16)", "external_references": [{"source_name": "source", "url": "hxxps://securityaffairs[.]com/192222/hacking/openai-hit-by-supply-chain-attack-linked-to-malicious-tanstack-packages[.]html"}], "labels": ["supply chain", "openai", "npm", "breach", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--8d6b664c-cf98-5c6a-9909-3f6943706655", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "note--877d756c-12dc-5aa6-b4a1-ed06f067d8c9", "target_ref": "threat-actor--71d345dd-e791-5866-873a-cc571c0f48ad", "description": "Breach note linked to referenced object", "labels": ["supply chain", "openai", "npm", "breach", "note-link", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--11399411-d0af-5f5a-b879-0c6b5fa68a20", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "note--877d756c-12dc-5aa6-b4a1-ed06f067d8c9", "target_ref": "identity--9dc18f4c-569a-5eec-ba61-40453db739f8", "description": "Breach note linked to referenced object", "labels": ["supply chain", "openai", "npm", "breach", "note-link", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "identity", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "identity--3742935d-a523-5f76-a407-b13e2f86e341", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "name": "HIQ (MSP) & 60 Clients", "identity_class": "organization", "labels": ["victim", "msp", "quest", "auth bypass", "breach", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "note", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "note--04a4206e-4574-5585-933b-0e298baba009", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "content": "## Summary\n**FR:** Compromission massive de plus de 60 organisations via le MSP HIQ, suite \u00e0 l'exploitation d'une faille CVSS 10 dans Quest KACE SMA (CVE-2025-32975).\n\n**EN:** Mass compromise of over 60 organizations via the MSP HIQ, following the exploitation of a CVSS 10 flaw in Quest KACE SMA (CVE-2025-32975).\n\n## Context\n- Date: 2026-05-16\n- Victim: HIQ (MSP) & 60 Clients\n- Threat actor: (unknown)\n- Sector: ['Services aux entreprises', 'Sant\u00e9 et Sciences de la vie'] / ['Business_Services', 'Healthcare_and_Life_Sciences']\n\n## Tags\nmsp, quest, auth bypass\n\n## Sources\n- hxxps://securityonline[.]info/quest-kace-sma-vulnerability-cve-2025-32975-exploited-cvss-10/\n", "object_refs": ["identity--3742935d-a523-5f76-a407-b13e2f86e341"], "abstract": "Breach | HIQ (MSP) & 60 Clients (2026-05-16)", "external_references": [{"source_name": "source", "url": "hxxps://securityonline[.]info/quest-kace-sma-vulnerability-cve-2025-32975-exploited-cvss-10/"}], "labels": ["msp", "quest", "auth bypass", "breach", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "relationship", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "relationship--91039170-4ca3-5236-9e18-24b501ddca34", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "note--04a4206e-4574-5585-933b-0e298baba009", "target_ref": "identity--3742935d-a523-5f76-a407-b13e2f86e341", "description": "Breach note linked to referenced object", "labels": ["msp", "quest", "auth bypass", "b