ified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "relationship_type": "related-to", "source_ref": "vulnerability--4d2a247c-8d63-5330-b189-4fff6688da29", "target_ref": "software--0d3b911f-cf04-5fe5-bc5b-b7d42ccd9278", "description": "Affected software identified from vendor/product/CPE metadata", "labels": ["vulnerability", "exchange", "xss", "kev", "viglintel", "daily-report"], "object_marking_refs": ["marking-definition--613f2e26-407d-48c7-9eca-b8e91df99dc9", "marking-definition--ad15a0cd-55b6-4588-a14c-a66105329b92"]}, {"type": "note", "spec_version": "2.1", "id": "note--25e4c6a0-6e51-5c97-92ce-94dc4b4994e2", "created": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "modified": "2026-05-16T00:00:00Z", "created_by_ref": "identity--1dc08bb0-1b9a-5415-b578-aacc99ac99ea", "content": "## Summary\n**FR:** Une vuln\u00e9rabilit\u00e9 de type Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) dans Outlook Web Access (OWA) permet \u00e0 un attaquant non autoris\u00e9 d'effectuer du spoofing via un email malveillant.\n\n**EN:** A Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability in Outlook Web Access (OWA) allows an unauthorized attacker to perform network spoofing via a malicious email.\n\n## Details\n- CVE: CVE-2026-42897\n- Vendor: Microsoft\n- Product: Microsoft Exchange Server\n- CPE: cpe:/a:microsoft:exchange_server\n- CVSS: 8.1\n- EPSS: (unknown)\n- CISA KEV: TRUE\n\n## Sources\n- hxxps://securityaffairs[.]com/192240/hacking/u-s-cisa-adds-a-flaw-in-microsoft-exchange-server-to-its-known-exploited-vulnerabilities-catalog[.]html\n", "object_refs": ["vulnerability--4d2a247c-8d63-5330-b189-4fff6688da29", "software--0d3b911f-cf04-5fe5-bc5b-b7d42ccd9278"], "abstract": "Vulnerability | CVE-2026-42897 (2026-05-16)", "external_references": [{"source_name": "source", "url": "hxxps://securityaffairs[.]com/192240/hacking/u-s-cisa-adds-a-flaw-in-microsoft-exchange-server-to-its-known-exploited-vulnerabilities-catalog[.]html"}], "labels": ["vulnerability", "exchange", "xss", "kev", "vi